New Records: Texas Rangers won their first World Series title in franchise history
Corey Seager won the World Series MVP award for the second time
Key Match Events: Texas Rangers scored three consecutive hits in the top of the seventh inning
Arizona Diamondbacks stranded runners in scoring position multiple times
Corey Seager homered three times and drove in six runs
Josh Sborz struck out Ketel Marte for the final out
Diamondbacks pitcher Zac Gallen kept Texas hitless through six innings
Post-Match Reflections: Marcus Semien expressed pride in the team's resilience
Corey Seager expressed gratitude for being part of the team
Bruce Bochy reflected on the victory as a pivotal moment in their playoff push
Miscellaneous Highlights: Texas Rangers had not won a World Series in 52 years
Arizona Diamondbacks last won the World Series in 2001
